The paper focuses on studying the impact of online activities in OSNs and formulating the influence maximization problem for social-activity networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Cybersecurity and Privacy (cs.CYBER), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
